      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">During a clinical study on muscle contractions in amphibians, medical students recorded a graph with a latent period of 10 ms, a contraction period of 40 ms, and a relaxation period of 20 ms. What is the tetanizing frequency based on these findings?</span></span></span></p>",
