      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A 30-year-old researcher is studying the mechanisms of neurotransmitter release at the neuromuscular junction. She focuses on the role of calcium in acetylcholine release and the type of channels activated by action potentials in the presynaptic terminal. Based on this context, evaluate the following statements regarding neuromuscular transmission:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Statement A:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"> Increased influx of calcium in the </span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">presynaptic<span style=\"color:black\"> terminal will facilitate the release of </span>acetylcholine<span style=\"color:black\"> in the neuromuscular junction</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Statement B:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"> Ligand gated calcium channels will be activated when the action potential reaches the </span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">presynaptic<span style=\"color:black\">terminal</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Which of the following is correct about these statements?</span></span></span></span></p>",
